     margins. Expanding this category with new SKUs would lift overall
     profitability.
  3. WASTE REDUCTION: Implement markdown promotions for items within
     7 days of expiry to clear stock and recover cost rather than
     discarding it.
{'='*65}
""")

# Bonus — Discount clearance simulation
df20_bonus = df20.copy()
df20_bonus['NewRevenue'] = df20_bonus['Revenue'].copy()
mask_rem   = df20_bonus['RemainingStock'] > 100
mask_exp   = df20_bonus['ExpiryDays'] < 5
# Apply discounts to remaining stock that would otherwise go unsold
df20_bonus.loc[mask_rem, 'NewRevenue'] += df20_bonus.loc[mask_rem, 'RemainingStock'] * \
    df20_bonus.loc[mask_rem, 'UnitPrice'] * 0.80   # 20% discount on remaining
df20_bonus.loc[mask_exp, 'NewRevenue'] += df20_bonus.loc[mask_exp, 'RemainingStock'] * \
    df20_bonus.loc[mask_exp, 'UnitPrice'] * 0.60   # 40% discount on expiring

orig_profit = df20['Profit'].sum()
new_profit  = (df20_bonus['NewRevenue'] - df20_bonus['CostPriceTotal']).sum()
print(f"BONUS — Original Profit: ${orig_profit:,.2f}  |  After Clearance: ${new_profit:,.2f}")

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 4))
ax.bar(['Original Profit', 'After Clearance'], [orig_profit, new_profit],
       color=['steelblue', 'mediumseagreen'], edgecolor='black')
ax.set_title("Original vs Clearance-Discount Profit")
ax.set_ylabel("Profit ($)")
for i, v in enumerate([orig_profit, new_profit]):
    ax.text(i, v + 20, f"${v:,.0f}", ha='center', fontweight='bold')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig(f"{OUTPUT}/q20_discount_comparison.png", dpi=100)
plt.close()
print("Clearance comparison saved: q20_discount_comparison.png")

print("\nAll charts saved to /mnt/user-data/outputs/")
